    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "For `plt.scatter` `c` defaults to `'b'` as [per the code here](https://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib/blob/master/lib/matplotlib/axes/_axes.py#L3623-L3627).\n\nNote that I think it's also possible to have RGBA tuples, I'll see if I can test whether having an RGBA tuple causes 4 points to do the same thing. So I suppose it'd have to be `len(df) <= 4` or some such?\n\nEDIT:\n\nYes if you had an RGBA tuple then having four points would cause the same issue. For example:\n\n``` python\nfrom pandas import DataFrame #0.16.0\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt #1.4.3\n#import seaborn as sns #0.5.1\nimport numpy as np #1.9.2\n\nplt.rcParams['patch.facecolor'] = (0.0, 0.33, 0.66, 1.0)\n\ndf = DataFrame({'x': np.random.uniform(0, 1, 4), 'y': np.random.uniform(0, 1, 4)})\n#df = DataFrame({'x': np.random.uniform(0, 1, 3), 'y': np.random.uniform(0, 1, 3)})\ndf.plot(kind = 'scatter', x = 'x', y = 'y')\nplt.show()\n```\n"
